    <preface>
      <p>
        <docNumber>80/239.</docNumber>
        <docTitle refersTo="#resolutionTitle">
          <span class="bold">Financing of the International Residual Mechanism for Criminal Tribunals</span>
        </docTitle>
      </p>
    </preface>
    <preamble>
      <formula name="enactingFormula" eId="formula_1">
        <p xml:space="preserve">
          <span class="italic">The General Assembly</span>,</p>
      </formula>
      <container name="Having considered" eId="container_2">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Having considered</span> the reports of the Secretary-General on the budget performance for 2024 and the proposed budget for 2026,<authorialNote marker="1" placement="bottom" eId="authorialNote_1"><p xml:space="preserve">		<a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/80/412">A/80/412</a>, <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/80/412/Corr.1">A/80/412/Corr.1</a> and <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/80/505">A/80/505</a>.</p></authorialNote> the financial report and audited financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2024 and the report of the Board of Auditors on the International Residual Mechanism for Criminal Tribunals<authorialNote marker="2" placement="bottom" eId="authorialNote_2"><p xml:space="preserve">		<span class="italic">	Official Records of the General Assembly, Eightieth Session, Supplement No. 5O</span> (<a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/80/5/Add.15">A/80/5/Add.15</a>).</p></authorialNote> and the recommendations contained therein, as well as the related report of the Advisory Committee on Administrative and Budgetary Questions,<authorialNote marker="3" placement="bottom" eId="authorialNote_3"><p xml:space="preserve">		<a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/80/570">A/80/570</a>.</p></authorialNote></p>
      </container>
      <container name="Recalling" eId="container_3">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recalling</span> its resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/RES/66/240">66/240</a> A of 24 December 2011 on the financing of the International Residual Mechanism for Criminal Tribunals and its subsequent resolutions thereon, the latest of which was resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/RES/79/255">79/255</a> of 24 December 2024, </p>
      </container>
    </preamble>
    <mainBody>
      <paragraph eId="para_4" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>1.</num>
        <content eId="para_4__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Takes note</span> of the reports of the Secretary-General; </p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_5" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>2.</num>
        <content eId="para_5__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Endorses</span> the conclusions and recommendations contained in the report of the Advisory Committee on Administrative and Budgetary Questions; </p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_7" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>3.</num>
        <content eId="para_7__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Decides</span> to appropriate to the special account for the International Residual Mechanism for Criminal Tribunals a total amount of 56,126,600 United States dollars gross (51,268,200 dollars net) for the Mechanism for 2026, as detailed in annex I to the present resolution; </p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_10" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>4.</num>
        <content eId="para_10__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Also decides</span> to apportion the amount of 28,063,300 dollars gross (25,634,100 dollars net) among Member States in accordance with the scale of assessments applicable to the regular budget of the United Nations for 2026;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_14" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>5.</num>
        <content eId="para_14__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Further decides</span> to apportion the amount of 28,063,300 dollars gross (25,634,100 dollars net) among Member States in accordance with the scale of assessments applicable to peacekeeping operations of the United Nations for 2026;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_19" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>6.</num>
        <content eId="para_19__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Decides</span> that, in accordance with the provisions of its resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/RES/973(X)">973 (X)</a> of 15 December 1955, there shall be set off against the apportionment among Member States, as provided for in paragraphs 4 and 5 above, their respective share in the Tax Equalization Fund of the estimated staff assessment income in the amount of 4,858,400 dollars approved for the Mechanism for 2026;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_25" class="MercuryDocument">
        <num>7.</num>
        <list eId="para_25_list">
          <intro eId="para_25_list_intro">
            <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Also decides</span>, in accordance with paragraph 4 of section XIV of its resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/RES/80/243">80/</a><a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/RES/80/243">243</a> of 30 December 2025 on the financial performance report on the programme budget for 2024, that there shall be a credit to Member States for their respective share of the credit of 8,898,000 dollars gross (9,756,600 dollars net), as reflected in the financial performance report on the budget of the International Residual Mechanism for Criminal Tribunals for 2024<authorialNote marker="4" placement="bottom" eId="authorialNote_4"><p xml:space="preserve">		<a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/80/412">A/80/412</a> and <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/80/412/Corr.1">A/80/412/Corr.1</a>.</p></authorialNote> and detailed in annex II to the present resolution:</p>
          </intro>
          <point eId="para_25_list_point_a">
            <num>(a)</num>
            <content eId="para_25_list_point_a_content">
              <p xml:space="preserve">	For Member States that have fulfilled their financial obligations to the Mechanism, as an offset against their assessment for 2026;</p>
            </content>
          </point>
          <point eId="para_25_list_point_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <content eId="para_25_list_point_b_content">
              <p xml:space="preserve">	For Member States that have not fulfilled their financial obligations to the Mechanism, as an offset against their arrears.</p>
            </content>
          </point>
        </list>
      </paragraph>
    </mainBody>
